metadata.name: Karakol Dream Beauty
metadata.description:
I saw the Photo of this valley (karakol) in Kyrgyzstan online back in 2018. Afterwards, it became my dream to visit the place and shoot it with my camera.

In may 2019, I went to Kyrgyzstan on a solo trip for 25 days to live my dream.

Karakol valley was the first destination on my itinerary. I was excited & looking forward to the day but road to dreams wasn't always so easy.
So, some unexpected events and trouble were bound to happen. When I reached the city, bad weather and snow started. I was told not to go up there and stay in the town.

I was really disappointed but i didn't give up. After 2 days of wait, I got lucky and started my dream journey.

When i saw this mountains in front of my eyes, I got lost in that moment and realised that dreams come true. 
It was such a magical and peaceful moment. That's why Nature holds a precious place in my life.

Comes with Physical metal print ( 36X24) inches on demand to the first collector.
